The theoretical foundations for such series are given by Broadhurst, for the first formula, and Ramanujan, for the second formula. The algorithms for fast evaluation of the Catalan constant were constructed by E. Karatsuba. Using these series, calculating Catalan&#x27;s constant is now about as fast as calculating Apéry&#x27;s constant, formula_7.

Other quickly converging series, due to Guillera and Pilehrood and employed by the y-cruncher software, include:

