formula_17

Simon Plouffe gives an infinite collection of identities between the trigamma function, 2 and Catalan&#x27;s constant; these are expressible as paths on a graph.

Catalan&#x27;s constant occurs frequently in relation to the Clausen function, the inverse tangent integral, the inverse sine integral, the Barnes -function, as well as integrals and series summable in terms of the aforementioned functions.

